WEBVTT

00:07.094 --> 00:08.965
It's happening again.

00:09.009 --> 00:11.359
Rosa, Rosa, Hitchcock fell
asleep in the break room.

00:11.402 --> 00:12.925
I pranked him.
I tied his shoelaces together.

00:12.969 --> 00:14.275
- You're 38 years old,
dude.

00:14.318 --> 00:16.103
- I know, and yet my pranks
still stay so fresh.

00:16.146 --> 00:17.408
It's incredible.

00:17.452 --> 00:19.149
- You gotta untie his shoes
before he gets hurt.

00:19.193 --> 00:20.846
- Look, seriously?

00:20.890 --> 00:22.848
- Seriously.
-  Fine.

00:22.892 --> 00:24.676
But what's the worst thing
that could happen?

00:25.677 --> 00:26.809
- He's being strangled
to death!

00:26.852 --> 00:27.853
- How?

00:53.140 --> 00:55.968
- So you still annoyed?
- Yes.

00:56.012 --> 00:57.666
You can't keep saying
"mischief managed"

00:57.709 --> 00:59.102
after we finish sex.

00:59.146 --> 01:00.364
It's what Harry Potter says

01:00.408 --> 01:01.583
when he needs to clear
the Marauder's Map.

01:01.626 --> 01:04.064
- Obviously, I know that,
but I would prefer

01:04.107 --> 01:06.196
to keep wizard terms
out of our sex life.

01:06.240 --> 01:07.589
- But what we're doing
is magical.

01:07.632 --> 01:08.590
We're making a baby.

01:10.113 --> 01:11.288
- Wait, why'd you stop
the elevator?

01:11.332 --> 01:15.075
- Look, I know you're excited,
and I am too,

01:15.118 --> 01:16.424
but I really don't
want to talk

01:16.467 --> 01:18.556
about us trying to get pregnant
while we're at work.

01:18.600 --> 01:20.428
You haven't said anything
to Charles, right?

01:20.471 --> 01:22.169
- No, and it's killing me.

01:22.212 --> 01:24.127
I still don't get why you can
tell Rosa but I can't tell him.

01:24.171 --> 01:25.389
- Rosa's low key.

01:25.433 --> 01:26.477
- Charles can be low key.

01:26.521 --> 01:28.000
- So how was
everyone's weekend?

01:28.044 --> 01:29.393
- Oh, uh,
we bought a couch.

01:29.437 --> 01:31.526
- Hoo-hoo,
tell me everything!

01:31.569 --> 01:34.137
- Okay, fine,
he can be a bit much.

01:34.181 --> 01:35.704
But don't worry.

01:35.747 --> 01:37.836
I have a plan that guarantees
I'm not gonna tell him.

01:37.880 --> 01:39.534
I've cut him out of my life
completely.

01:39.577 --> 01:40.665
- That doesn't
seem sustainable.

01:40.709 --> 01:42.841
- Yeah, well, so far,
it's working

01:42.885 --> 01:44.191
and it's foolproof,
so--

01:44.234 --> 01:45.409
- Morning!

01:45.453 --> 01:46.628
Jake, can I talk to you
for a second?

01:46.671 --> 01:47.846
- Mm-hmm.

01:47.890 --> 01:49.239
- I feel like we haven't
hung out in forever.

01:49.283 --> 01:50.588
- Oh, is that so? I didn't
realize. Is that the case?

01:50.632 --> 01:52.068
- You wanna get a drink
after work tonight?

01:52.112 --> 01:53.983
I'm dying to tell you
about Genevieve's new shampoo.

01:54.026 --> 01:55.027
It's edible.

01:55.071 --> 01:56.377
- Oh, wow,
that sounds so fun,

01:56.420 --> 01:59.728
but I actually...can't
because I have plans

01:59.771 --> 02:01.991
with Ron Weasley...berg.
It's a friend of Amy's.

02:02.034 --> 02:04.559
The point is, I'm unavailable
for a very real reason.

02:04.602 --> 02:05.647
- Jake!

02:05.690 --> 02:06.865
- Oh, my God, is that...
- Boyle!

02:06.909 --> 02:08.040
- It does sound like...

02:08.084 --> 02:10.260
It's me, Adrian Pimento.

02:10.304 --> 02:11.392
- Yeah, we know.

02:11.435 --> 02:12.610
Hi, Adrian.
How are you?

02:12.654 --> 02:15.265
- Very bad, someone's
trying to kill me.

02:15.309 --> 02:17.006
- Before we wrap up
this briefing,

02:17.049 --> 02:19.139
I wanted to give
a few shout-outs.

02:19.182 --> 02:21.228
Diaz, great job on that B&E.

02:21.271 --> 02:23.926
You are a good cop
with a great attitude.

02:23.969 --> 02:25.971
- I don't like this.
- Santiago, when I think

02:26.015 --> 02:29.671
of your CompStat reports,
one word comes to mind: wow.

02:29.714 --> 02:32.500
And that "WOW" is an acronym
for "wow, oh, wow."

02:32.543 --> 02:33.936
- What is happening?
- He's buttering us up

02:33.979 --> 02:36.417
before giving us some
devastatingly bad news.

02:36.460 --> 02:37.940
My God, Jake and Charles
are dead.

02:39.159 --> 02:40.508
- Jake and Charles
are not dead.

02:40.551 --> 02:41.726
It's worse than that.

02:41.770 --> 02:43.467
We have to do
our annual HR seminar

02:43.511 --> 02:44.990
on workplace conflict
tomorrow.

02:45.034 --> 02:46.166
- What? Already?

02:46.209 --> 02:47.950
- I know.
I know.

02:47.993 --> 02:50.300
These seminars are not exactly
our favorite things.

02:50.344 --> 02:51.432
- Question:
if I get shot

02:51.475 --> 02:52.911
in the line of duty,
can I miss it?

02:52.955 --> 02:54.043
- Legally, you still
have to make it up.

02:54.086 --> 02:55.392
- Well, there goes
that plan.

02:55.436 --> 02:58.003
- Sir, it's a seminar
that's too boring for me.

02:58.047 --> 03:00.092
I'm saying no to a seminar.

03:00.136 --> 03:01.920
- Look, it's mandatory,
it's not up for debate,

03:01.964 --> 03:03.226
but we'll get through it

03:03.270 --> 03:05.185
'cause we're the best squad
in the city

03:05.228 --> 03:07.709
with the nicest hair,
the kindest eyes.

03:07.752 --> 03:09.885
- He's buttering us up again,
so more bad news is coming.

03:10.886 --> 03:12.453
- HR said they're
sending a funny guy.

03:12.496 --> 03:14.498
- No!

03:14.542 --> 03:17.501
- All I know is, I woke up
in a pool of my own blood

03:17.545 --> 03:19.982
next to a metal chair
that had a dent in it

03:20.025 --> 03:22.332
the same shape as my head.

03:22.376 --> 03:23.551
- What were you doing
before the attack?

03:23.594 --> 03:25.379
- I was sitting in said
metal chair watching

03:25.422 --> 03:27.729
the season two premiere
of "The Masked Singer."

03:27.772 --> 03:28.817
The Egg had just gone,

03:28.860 --> 03:30.688
and I'm pretty sure
I know who it is,

03:30.732 --> 03:31.689
Sara Gilbert.

03:31.733 --> 03:32.777
- That doesn't
make any sense.

03:32.821 --> 03:33.909
- Are you kidding?

03:33.952 --> 03:35.389
You don't think I know
how Darlene walks?

03:35.432 --> 03:36.868
- No, no, no, no,
I'm sure you do,

03:36.912 --> 03:39.436
it's just "The Masked Singer"
ended four months ago.

03:39.480 --> 03:41.046
I still can't believe
that the Bowl of Ramen

03:41.090 --> 03:42.134
wasn't Dikembe Mutombo.

03:42.178 --> 03:43.135
- Four month--
no, no, no.

03:43.179 --> 03:44.702
I watched this last night.

03:44.746 --> 03:46.661
That doesn't make any--

03:46.704 --> 03:48.489
Where am I?

03:48.532 --> 03:50.491
What is that table?
- Calm down.

03:50.534 --> 03:52.928
You're at the nine-nine,
and you know what a table is.

03:52.971 --> 03:54.451
- I don't remember coming here.
How did I get here?

03:54.495 --> 03:56.410
- Oh, my God.

03:56.453 --> 03:58.281
Pimento has
"Memento" disease.

03:58.325 --> 03:59.804
Your memory
is resetting

03:59.848 --> 04:02.329
like the guy from
the movie "Memento."

04:02.372 --> 04:03.721
- What?
- You guys never saw "Memento"?

04:03.765 --> 04:05.549
It's the guy with
no short-term memory,

04:05.593 --> 04:07.203
you know, Christopher Nolan's
first movie.

04:07.247 --> 04:08.900
- Is it like Dory
from "Finding Dory,"

04:08.944 --> 04:10.250
she keeps forgetting
where she's swimming?

04:10.293 --> 04:12.513
- No, no, it's like--
- Dory, yeah, yeah, yeah!

04:12.556 --> 04:14.384
I'm like the forgetful
little fish.

04:14.428 --> 04:15.994
- Ah.
- Oh, I mean, yeah, it's like

04:16.038 --> 04:17.605
that, but it's also like--
- Just keep swimming!

04:17.648 --> 04:19.433
- That's what Dory says.
- Classic Dory, Jake!

04:19.476 --> 04:20.738
- Ugh, you guys
really ruined

04:20.782 --> 04:22.305
the coolness of this
"Memento" thing.

04:22.349 --> 04:23.741
- Also, Jake, "Following"

04:23.785 --> 04:25.308
is Christopher Nolan's
first movie.

04:25.352 --> 04:27.441
You sound like a grade A
out here.

04:28.398 --> 04:29.878
- What's up, squad?

04:29.921 --> 04:32.750
Hope y'all like condiments
because I got all the sauce.

04:32.794 --> 04:34.012
- Huh?

04:34.056 --> 04:35.623
- I arrested a tween shoplifter
yesterday,

04:35.666 --> 04:38.016
and she was real cool
at talking.

04:38.060 --> 04:40.932
- I love you, Amy, but maybe
slang isn't your thing.

04:40.976 --> 04:42.630
Whatevs.

04:42.673 --> 04:44.371
Check it: I got a copy

04:44.414 --> 04:46.634
of last year's workplace
conflict presentation.

04:46.677 --> 04:49.680
All we have to do
is study the crap out of it,

04:49.724 --> 04:51.334
then we can answer
every question

04:51.378 --> 04:53.989
before that tool from HR
even asks it.

04:54.032 --> 04:55.599
We'll be done in no time.

04:55.643 --> 04:57.601
- So your solution for getting
us out of the boring seminar

04:57.645 --> 04:59.777
is having us memorize
the boring seminar.

04:59.821 --> 05:00.735
- Exactly.

05:00.778 --> 05:02.606
- It's genius,
and it's fun.

05:02.650 --> 05:03.868
I love committing things
to memory.

05:03.912 --> 05:05.479
- Yeah, I'm out.
I don't do homework.

05:05.522 --> 05:07.089
- You do now.

05:07.132 --> 05:09.787
Get busy, ya flope.
- Flope?

05:09.831 --> 05:11.963
- It means loser, okay?
It's new slang.

05:12.007 --> 05:14.357
People are saying it!
The tween said so!

05:14.401 --> 05:15.837
- It just doesn't
make any sense.

05:15.880 --> 05:17.317
I mean, you love
"The Dark Knight,"

05:17.360 --> 05:18.492
you love "Inception,"

05:18.535 --> 05:20.232
and you haven't even
seen"Memento"?

05:20.276 --> 05:21.625
- Jake, I don't know
what to tell ya.

05:21.669 --> 05:23.105
I spend a lot of time
in jungles, you know.

05:23.148 --> 05:24.802
They don't exactly
get movies like that.

05:24.846 --> 05:27.022
It's usually big blockbusters
like "Finding Dory."

05:27.065 --> 05:28.632
- 486 million domestic.

05:28.676 --> 05:30.982
- When you factor in
international, 1.2 billion.

05:31.026 --> 05:33.420
- Look, Adrian, we don't
have a ton to go off on here.

05:33.463 --> 05:34.595
What else has been
going on in your life?

05:34.638 --> 05:35.639
- Normal stuff.

05:35.683 --> 05:37.162
Ooh, I got hired as a PI

05:37.206 --> 05:38.947
by the Countess Luann
from "Real Housewives."

05:38.990 --> 05:41.863
I ended up sleeping with her
in a tiny hotel Jacuzzi.

05:41.906 --> 05:43.647
I also microwaved
a watermelon

05:43.691 --> 05:44.822
just to see if
it would explode.

05:44.866 --> 05:46.476
- Okay, this is
immediately unhelpful,

05:46.520 --> 05:49.218
but did
the watermelon explode?

05:49.261 --> 05:50.785
- It just cracked
and got hot.

05:50.828 --> 05:52.482
- Oh.
- Total bust.

05:52.526 --> 05:53.483
- Hey, maybe
one of your PI cases

05:53.527 --> 05:54.658
is the reason
you got attacked.

05:54.702 --> 05:56.486
- I thought of that too,
but I doubt it.

05:56.530 --> 05:58.836
You know, they're all the same,
kinda boring.

05:58.880 --> 06:02.362
It's some redheaded lady wants
me to hack her husband's phone

06:02.405 --> 06:05.452
to see if he's cheating with
a spin instructor named Kendra.

06:05.495 --> 06:06.670
- It seems a little specific

06:06.714 --> 06:08.106
that they would all
be like that, but okay.

06:09.194 --> 06:10.500
- Where is that
coming from?

06:10.544 --> 06:11.980
- Oh, my God,
there's a bomb in my chest!

06:12.023 --> 06:13.634
- What?
- They put a bomb in my chest!

06:13.677 --> 06:15.070
- What do we do?

06:17.681 --> 06:19.422
Wait a second, the sound's
coming from my little watch.

06:20.728 --> 06:22.425
- You just assumed
there was a bomb inside you?

06:22.469 --> 06:26.603
- It says, "Take pill,
right jacket po"--

06:26.647 --> 06:29.563
I've never seen these
before in my life.

06:29.606 --> 06:31.260
- This was filled
three days ago.

06:31.303 --> 06:34.263
This doctor must be
treating you for your...

06:34.306 --> 06:36.047
- "Finding Dory" Disease,

06:36.091 --> 06:38.223
that's what most people call
anterograde amnesia.

06:38.267 --> 06:39.573
both: Just keep swimming.

06:39.616 --> 06:41.444
- Exactly, that's what
I tell my patients,

06:41.488 --> 06:42.880
just keep swimming.

06:42.924 --> 06:44.708
- So what do you think
caused Pimento's memory loss?

06:44.752 --> 06:46.710
- Probably years
of repeated head trauma.

06:46.754 --> 06:48.451
I've been working
as a neurologist

06:48.495 --> 06:51.846
for over two decades,
and I have neverseen a patient

06:51.889 --> 06:53.630
with more traumatic
head injuries.

06:53.674 --> 06:54.805
- Well, doesn't look so bad.

06:54.849 --> 06:56.241
- The red
is the good parts.

06:56.285 --> 06:57.417
- Oh, my God.

06:57.460 --> 06:58.461
Oh, I guess
it does make sense.

06:58.505 --> 06:59.680
Pimento lives pretty hard.

06:59.723 --> 07:00.942
- I locked my keys
in the car again.

07:00.985 --> 07:02.596
I guess I'll have
to smash the window.

07:02.639 --> 07:04.119
- Actually, I got
a hammer in my car.

07:06.208 --> 07:07.339
Come on,
everybody knows

07:07.383 --> 07:09.080
the skull is the hammer
of the body.

07:09.124 --> 07:10.430
- Yeah, that's not true.

07:10.473 --> 07:11.605
- What? Really?

07:11.648 --> 07:13.781
Okay, well,
then this is on me.

07:13.824 --> 07:15.609
- Look, this morning,
Pimento was screaming

07:15.652 --> 07:16.914
about someone
trying to kill him.

07:16.958 --> 07:18.263
Has he said anything
like that to you?

07:18.307 --> 07:20.527
- He has, but I've seen him
every day for weeks,

07:20.570 --> 07:22.050
and I haven't noticed
any new injuries,

07:22.093 --> 07:25.401
but the medication he's on
may be making him paranoid.

07:25.445 --> 07:26.663
- Really? Because he doesn't--

07:26.707 --> 07:28.578
There's a bomb in my chest!

07:29.797 --> 07:31.538
- Right, he does keep
doing that.

07:32.756 --> 07:34.018
- Hey, it was nice of you

07:34.062 --> 07:35.280
to let Pimento crash
at your place last night.

07:35.324 --> 07:36.281
How'd it go?

07:36.325 --> 07:37.326
- Oh, well, he gave Nikolaj

07:37.369 --> 07:38.719
a haircut
while he was asleep,

07:38.762 --> 07:41.199
but no weird memory stuff,
so all in all, major win.

07:41.243 --> 07:42.984
- Great, so it sounds like
he might be getting better.

07:43.027 --> 07:44.768
- Ah, someone's
trying to kill me!

07:44.812 --> 07:45.943
- Oh, boy,
here we go again.

07:45.987 --> 07:48.598
- Ah, gah!
- Pimento, Pimento, Pimento!

07:48.642 --> 07:50.339
Don't worry.
Everything's okay.

07:50.382 --> 07:51.514
You've had
some brain trauma,

07:51.558 --> 07:52.776
and it caused you
to lose your memory.

07:52.820 --> 07:54.430
You're scared
that you're in danger,

07:54.474 --> 07:56.737
but there is no evidence that
anyone is trying to kill you.

07:56.780 --> 07:58.129
You're safe.
- Wait, wait, really?

07:58.173 --> 08:00.131
Whew, okay.

08:00.175 --> 08:01.742
Thank you.

08:01.785 --> 08:03.134
I was really worried, you know,
'cause of this gunshot wound.

08:03.178 --> 08:04.962
- Oh, my God, someone's
trying to kill you!

08:05.006 --> 08:07.530
- What? You just told me
that wasn't the case!

08:09.750 --> 08:11.360
- So there I am, naked,

08:11.403 --> 08:12.535
still holding
the hedge trimmers

08:12.579 --> 08:14.798
when the chauffeur walks in
and I say,

08:14.842 --> 08:16.321
"Guess you caught me
red-handed."

08:16.365 --> 08:17.932
- Because of the blood?
- Yeah, because of the blood!

08:17.975 --> 08:18.933
See, you get it.

08:20.456 --> 08:21.936
- The bullet went through
your friend's shoulder.

08:21.979 --> 08:24.460
He should be fine,
although he does keep asking me

08:24.504 --> 08:25.983
if we do the "Face/Off"
surgery here.

08:26.027 --> 08:27.768
And what'd you tell him?

08:27.811 --> 08:29.160
- That we don't.

08:29.204 --> 08:30.510
Right.

08:31.598 --> 08:33.338
She's hiding something.
- Obviously.

08:33.382 --> 08:35.776
Okay, Adrian, there's very
little evidence to go on,

08:35.819 --> 08:37.865
so we should take a look
at your PI case files.

08:37.908 --> 08:39.257
- Don't have any.

08:39.301 --> 08:41.216
Keep everything right up here
in the old steel--

08:41.259 --> 08:42.260
where am I?

08:42.304 --> 08:43.479
What is this bed?

08:43.523 --> 08:44.785
- And his memory's
resetting.

08:44.828 --> 08:46.003
All right, Adrian,
someone's trying to kill you.

08:46.047 --> 08:47.439
- Uh-huh.
- You have a memory disorder...

08:47.483 --> 08:49.354
- That makes sense.
- Like in the movie "Memento."

08:49.398 --> 08:51.356
- I haven't seen that!
- It's like "Finding Dory."

08:51.400 --> 08:52.880
- Oh, now I know
exactly what's going on.

08:52.923 --> 08:53.924
Thank you, Charles.

08:53.968 --> 08:55.186
- Okay, let's get you dressed

08:55.230 --> 08:56.492
and back to the precinct
where it's safe.

08:56.536 --> 08:57.841
- Okay.

08:57.885 --> 08:59.364
- Oh, Adrian, the back
of your gown's open.

08:59.408 --> 09:01.149
- Don't peek at my tushy.

09:01.192 --> 09:03.717
- Ah. Wait, since when is
your back covered in tattoos?

09:03.760 --> 09:05.153
- It's not,

09:05.196 --> 09:07.198
otherwise I couldn't get buried
in a Jewish cemetery.

09:07.242 --> 09:08.809
- Are you Jewish?
- Not yet.

09:08.852 --> 09:10.854
Ooh, I should ask that nurse if
they've got a mohel on staff.

09:10.898 --> 09:12.421
- Wait, maybe you've been
getting tattoos

09:12.464 --> 09:14.075
to help you remember things,
like the guy in "Memento."

09:14.118 --> 09:15.424
- Again, haven't seen it.

09:15.467 --> 09:17.165
- No, the tattoos
could be clues

09:17.208 --> 09:18.166
that you're leaving
for yourself.

09:18.209 --> 09:19.602
Here, we'll step out.

09:19.646 --> 09:21.212
You get undressed and write
down everything you see,

09:21.256 --> 09:23.388
and you're fully naked.
- Hey-oh!

09:23.432 --> 09:25.173
- All right, well, I guess
we're looking at 'em together.

09:26.261 --> 09:27.784
- My name is Brad Portenberg,

09:27.828 --> 09:31.571
and today I'm gonna teach you
about workplace conflict.

09:31.614 --> 09:35.052
So I brought along someone
who's an expert in conflict:

09:35.096 --> 09:36.445
my ex-wife.

09:38.186 --> 09:39.317
Just kidding.

09:39.361 --> 09:40.623
She lives in Vermont
with our kids.

09:40.667 --> 09:43.321
So can anyone tell me
what a stereotype is?

09:43.365 --> 09:45.062
- The Irish are
potato-eating drunks.

09:45.106 --> 09:46.455
- And the gays--
- No, no, no,

09:46.498 --> 09:48.675
what does the word
"stereotype" mean?

09:48.718 --> 09:50.372
- Uh...
- I got this, fellas.

09:50.415 --> 09:52.069
It's a preconceived,
often prejudiced notion

09:52.113 --> 09:53.680
about a group of people.

09:53.723 --> 09:55.595
- Great, and can anyone tell me
what a protected class is?

09:55.638 --> 09:57.553
- A group of people
with a common characteristic

09:57.597 --> 09:59.599
that is legally protected
from employment discrimination.

09:59.642 --> 10:00.774
- And how many protected
classes are there?

10:00.817 --> 10:01.775
