about this.

14:23.863 --> 14:26.126
Look, you're being unfair.

14:26.169 --> 14:27.301
There's some things
in my life with Amy

14:27.344 --> 14:28.345
that are just between
her and me,

14:28.389 --> 14:29.651
and I need you
to be okay with that.

14:29.694 --> 14:31.348
- Fine.

14:31.392 --> 14:33.220
You're right.
I get it.

14:33.263 --> 14:34.830
I mean, it's not like
you told anyone else.

14:34.874 --> 14:36.919
- Right.

14:36.963 --> 14:39.574
I mean...

14:39.617 --> 14:40.662
- We told Rosa.

14:40.705 --> 14:42.185
- Rosa, that dud?

14:42.229 --> 14:43.360
Oh, why her and not me?

14:43.404 --> 14:45.014
- Sometimes you can
be a little much.

14:45.058 --> 14:47.451
- A little much?
A little much!

14:47.495 --> 14:49.105
- Yes, a little much.

14:49.149 --> 14:51.716
- Well, maybe, Jake, I have
"Finding Dory" Disease too

14:51.760 --> 14:53.022
because right now,

14:53.066 --> 14:55.198
I can't remember
why we ever were friends!

14:55.242 --> 14:57.374
- Okay, see, once again,
that was a little over the top.

14:57.418 --> 15:01.509
- Excuse me, my godson's dad,
the crazy guy just ran away.

15:01.552 --> 15:02.945
- Oh, my God, he's gone.

15:02.989 --> 15:04.773
Pimento is gone.
- Just like our friendship!

15:04.816 --> 15:05.861
- Come on, Charles.

15:05.905 --> 15:07.384
- Well, I've got
a bean to boil too.

15:07.428 --> 15:10.648
Santiago always tries
to finish my sentences

15:10.692 --> 15:11.998
and frequently gets it wrong.

15:12.041 --> 15:14.043
- I do not,
and I am not wrong.

15:14.087 --> 15:16.350
- You do it all the--
- Time?

15:16.393 --> 15:19.135
- No, I was going to say,
