him to ruin his memory.

17:15.686 --> 17:17.340
Now where is he?
- I haven't see him.

17:17.384 --> 17:19.299
- Oh, please, you're making
this way too easy.

17:19.342 --> 17:20.735
You clearly just glanced
at this door.

17:20.778 --> 17:22.084
- Don't.
He's not in there.

17:22.128 --> 17:24.086
- Oh, really? Because I'm
pretty sure that he...

17:24.130 --> 17:25.218
isn't.

17:25.261 --> 17:26.175
But he clearly was.

17:26.219 --> 17:28.134
- Jake, help!

17:28.177 --> 17:29.570
- Pimento.

17:33.052 --> 17:33.965
- Got him.

17:34.009 --> 17:35.097
Help!

17:35.141 --> 17:36.185
Jake, what's happening?

17:36.229 --> 17:37.447
What is this ledge?

17:37.491 --> 17:39.145
- You must have tried
to escape out the window

17:39.188 --> 17:40.624
and then your
memory reset.

17:40.668 --> 17:41.930
- What?
I don't understand.

17:41.973 --> 17:43.279
Why would
my memory reset?

17:43.323 --> 17:46.978
- It's just like the film...

17:47.022 --> 17:48.154
"Finding Dory."

17:48.197 --> 17:50.286
- Huh?
- "Finding Dory."

17:50.330 --> 17:51.287
- Ah, say no more!

17:51.331 --> 17:53.115
I completely understand!

17:53.159 --> 17:54.682
- Just stay where you are.
I'm gonna come get you.

17:54.725 --> 17:55.987
- Okay.

17:56.031 --> 17:57.293
Should I go over here?

17:57.337 --> 17:58.599
- No, why would you
go over there?

17:58.642 --> 17:59.774
- I don't know!

17:59.817 --> 18:01.515
I just woke up out here!

18:01.558 --> 18:02.516
- Just stay still!

18:02.559 --> 18:04.170
- Ah, I don't know
what to do!

18:04.213 --> 18:06.520
- Okay, all right.
Here I come.

18:06.563 --> 18:07.564
Here I come.

18:07.608 --> 18:09.088
- Uh, I'm scared
of heights, Jake.

18:09.131 --> 18:11.220
- Yeah, so am I, Adrian.

18:11.264 --> 18:12.656
- This might not be
the time to tell you,

18:12.700 --> 18:15.616
but both my parents died
falling out of lighthouses,

18:15.659 --> 18:16.660
separate incidents.

18:16.704 --> 18:18.053
- Oh, man, I have
so many questions,

18:18.097 --> 18:20.011
but for now,
just follow my lead, okay?

18:20.055 --> 18:21.056
- Okay.

18:21.100 --> 18:22.144
- Take small
little baby steps,

18:22.188 --> 18:23.232
like this.

18:25.104 --> 18:26.105
- You're not moving!

18:26.148 --> 18:27.715
- I'm not?

18:27.758 --> 18:29.760
Oh, uh-oh.

18:32.937 --> 18:34.852
- Huh, I'm really
scared, Jake.

18:34.896 --> 18:36.245
I'm really scared.
- Yeah, I know,

18:36.289 --> 18:38.856
just try and look at one thing
and focus only on that

18:38.900 --> 18:40.380
until I can get Charles
out here to help.

18:40.423 --> 18:41.816
- Okay, okay.

18:41.859 --> 18:43.992
Ooh, there's a juicy
old person butt in that window.

18:44.035 --> 18:46.037
- Why's it gotta be
juicy and old?

18:46.081 --> 18:48.301
- I don't know,
but I'm grateful for it.

18:48.344 --> 18:49.780
- All right,
just lock in on that.

18:49.824 --> 18:51.913
Hey, Charles, I know
you're still mad at me

18:51.956 --> 18:53.436
for not telling you
Amy and I are trying,

18:53.480 --> 18:54.611
but I could really
use your help.

18:54.655 --> 18:56.004
- That's not all
I'm mad about, Jake.

18:56.047 --> 18:57.919
I'm upset because
you keep blowing me off.

18:57.962 --> 18:59.790
We haven't hung out
in weeks.

18:59.834 --> 19:01.314
We don't talk
on the phone anymore.

19:01.357 --> 19:03.707
I can't remember the last time
we painted pottery together.

19:03.751 --> 19:06.623
Sorry, I know this isn't
the time to talk about this.

19:06.667 --> 19:07.929
- No, no, no, keep going.

19:07.972 --> 19:09.148
It's helping to distract me
from the fact

19:09.191 --> 19:10.801
that I could fall
and instantly die.

19:10.845 --> 19:12.803
- Oh, no, from this height,
it wouldn't be instant.

19:12.847 --> 19:15.197
When you hit the ground,
your ribs would shatter,

19:15.241 --> 19:16.807
puncturing your lungs.

19:16.851 --> 19:19.941
You'd start to drown on
your own blood, gurgling and--

19:19.984 --> 19:21.160
- Okay, Adrian,
I'm being distracted

19:21.203 --> 19:22.291
by Charles right now,
thank you.

19:22.335 --> 19:23.336
- Okay.

19:23.379 --> 19:24.424
- Here, take--take my hand.

19:24.467 --> 19:25.816
I can guide you guys back.

19:25.860 --> 19:28.167
- Come on, we're a chain.
Here we go.

19:28.210 --> 19:30.081
- Just keep swimming.
- Oh, just keep swimming.

19:30.125 --> 19:31.431
- Just keep swimming.
- Oh, say it, Jake.

19:32.867 --> 19:33.824
Just keep swimming.

19:33.868 --> 19:35.130
- Good.
- Oh!

19:35.174 --> 19:36.436
- Hey, just so you know,

19:36.479 --> 19:37.654
the only reason
that I've been avoiding you

19:37.698 --> 19:39.047
is because I really
wanted to tell you

19:39.090 --> 19:40.222
what me and Amy
have been up to,

19:40.266 --> 19:41.484
and I knew the second
that I saw you,

19:41.528 --> 19:42.485
I would just blurt it out.

19:42.529 --> 19:43.834
I always
tell you everything.

19:43.878 --> 19:45.445
I hated not being able
to say anything.

19:45.488 --> 19:46.837
- Aw, that's so sweet.

19:46.881 --> 19:49.840
Your love for each other
is really wonderful.

19:49.884 --> 19:51.668
Let's hug.
Let's all hug.

19:51.712 --> 19:52.669
- Oh, no, no, no,
we're still on the ledge!

20:00.024 --> 20:02.375
Okay, this sucks.

20:02.418 --> 20:05.204
We never fight,
and then stupid Brad comes in

20:05.247 --> 20:06.683
and turns us
all against each other

20:06.727 --> 20:08.250
and now we're acting
like a bunch of kids.

20:08.294 --> 20:09.338
- Not all kids.

20:09.382 --> 20:10.513
My girls never act like this.

20:10.557 --> 20:11.732
- We may be arguing,

20:11.775 --> 20:13.864
but we're all thinking
the same thing:

20:13.908 --> 20:15.170
Terry talks about
his children too much.

20:15.214 --> 20:17.085
- Do I really?
You all think that?

20:17.128 --> 20:18.695
- Keep a lid on the box,
Pandora.

20:18.739 --> 20:19.696
You won't like what's inside.

20:19.740 --> 20:20.958
- Everybody, shut up.

20:21.002 --> 20:22.699
You're all acting
like a bunch of Ramonas.

20:22.743 --> 20:24.353
- Ramona?
- Yeah, she hated the smell

20:24.397 --> 20:26.616
of her coworker's holiday
candle, so she threw it out.

20:26.660 --> 20:28.227
It was in that thing
that you made us memorize.

20:28.270 --> 20:29.967
- You memorized it?

20:30.011 --> 20:31.882
But you said it was homework
and you don't do homework.

20:31.926 --> 20:33.710
- Yeah, well, you said
to read it, so I read it.

20:33.754 --> 20:35.364
We're a team, ya flope.

20:35.408 --> 20:36.757
- It's catching on.

20:36.800 --> 20:38.106
- Eh, I mean...

20:39.194 --> 20:41.152
- Hey, guys, it's me,
Adrian Pimento.

20:41.196 --> 20:43.242
- Hey, Pimento,
how's it going, bud?

20:43.285 --> 20:44.982
- Pretty good,
I know where I am,

20:45.026 --> 20:47.942
and I know what a table is,
so everything's going great.

20:47.985 --> 20:50.074
- Pretty low bar for greatness,
but all right.

20:50.118 --> 20:52.207
- Hey, how's it been since you
stopped taking those pills?

20:52.251 --> 20:55.645
- Well, thankfully,
my full memory has come back,

20:55.689 --> 20:57.778
even the things
that haunt me.

21:07.614 --> 21:09.790
Hey, Jake, I saw that movie
you keep talking about.

21:09.833 --> 21:12.314
- You watched "Memento"?
And what'd you think?

21:12.358 --> 21:14.751
- It's okay.

21:22.019 --> 21:24.021
- Not a doctor.
- Shh.

21:24.065 --> 21:26.110
- Fremulon.
